510
00:48:47,910 --> 00:48:52,090
But once things calmed down, I was finally able to see what I wanted to do.

511
00:48:53,690 --> 00:48:57,650
Of course, I'll have a part-time job and also help with expenditures.

512
00:48:57,700 --> 00:49:01,790
However, I wanted to hear your opinion on this.

513
00:49:03,010 --> 00:49:04,690
Do you think it's okay?

514
00:49:04,690 --> 00:49:08,470
Of course, it's fine!

515
00:49:08,500 --> 00:49:10,640
- Really? 
 - Yeah!

516
00:49:10,640 --> 00:49:14,630
You always were good at making up stories.

517
00:49:14,630 --> 00:49:21,330
Even now, those fantasy make-believe games we did back then have always remained with me in my heart.

518
00:49:21,330 --> 00:49:25,730
I thought it would be nice if I could always have fun like that.

519
00:49:27,180 --> 00:49:31,020
- So that's why you suggested a trip? To talk about that? 
 - Yeah.

520
00:49:31,020 --> 00:49:33,850
I think a lot of things will change from here on out.

521
00:49:33,850 --> 00:49:35,950
So I wanted to talk to you properly about it.

522
00:49:37,160 --> 00:49:38,760
Is that so?

523
00:49:41,530 --> 00:49:44,040
I'm so relieved that I could finally say it!

524
00:49:47,410 --> 00:49:49,250
So relieved.

525
00:49:53,530 --> 00:49:56,250
- Huh? 
 - What's wrong?

526
00:49:56,250 --> 00:49:59,900
- I can't find my Zippo lighter. 
 - Your favorite one?

527
00:50:01,240 --> 00:50:04,920
- I wonder if I dropped it somewhere while we were playing. 
 - Shall we search for it?

528
00:50:04,920 --> 00:50:08,430
No, it will be hard to find in the sandy plains.

529
00:50:08,430 --> 00:50:11,900
It's fine, let's go eat dinner.

530
00:50:38,720 --> 00:50:42,200
You want to have fun like back in those days forever?

531
00:50:43,150 --> 00:50:48,050
I never knew that you were thinking of things like that.

532
00:50:55,720 --> 00:51:00,230
I wonder if things between us will change, too.

533
00:51:50,950 --> 00:51:52,600
Yuki.

534
00:51:53,280 --> 00:51:54,960
Yuki?

535
00:52:56,060 --> 00:52:57,850
Yuki!

536
00:53:07,120 --> 00:53:08,840
Yuki...

537
00:53:13,890 --> 00:53:16,550
I found some gold in the desert!

538
00:53:27,040 --> 00:53:30,180
I wonder if we can buy a camel with this?

539
00:53:38,910 --> 00:53:40,940
Were you really that happy?

540
00:53:54,720 --> 00:53:59,810
[Twenty-eight]

541
00:54:14,230 --> 00:54:16,690
- Good morning. 
 - Morning.

542
00:54:18,240 --> 00:54:20,220
- Itou. 
 - Yes?

543
00:54:20,220 --> 00:54:22,360
The plans you designed the other day were great.

544
00:54:22,360 --> 00:54:24,330
- Thank you. 
 - The Planning Department complimented you.

545
00:54:24,330 --> 00:54:27,160
- I'm counting on you next time as well! 
 - I'll do my best!

546
00:54:30,550 --> 00:54:35,030
As long as we're together, there's nothing to fear.

547
00:54:35,030 --> 00:54:37,230
That's what I had believed.

548
00:54:40,300 --> 00:54:42,380
But ever since that day...

549
00:54:42,380 --> 00:54:45,580
A feeling of unease has been constantly following me around.

550
00:54:53,170 --> 00:54:55,440
I'm home.

551
00:54:55,440 --> 00:54:57,130
Welcome back.

552
00:55:01,160 --> 00:55:03,760
Are you still going to work?

553
00:55:03,760 --> 00:55:06,830
Sorry, I want to stick with doing this.

554
00:55:06,830 --> 00:55:09,560
I've finally decided on the topic after all.

555
00:55:12,990 --> 00:55:15,180
I'm going to bed then.

556
00:55:39,830 --> 00:55:44,970
At that time, more so than when we first met, that mature smile

557
00:55:44,970 --> 00:55:47,510
was really pretty, I thought.

558
00:55:50,790 --> 00:55:53,530
However, in the next moment...

559
00:55:53,530 --> 00:55:56,910
I imagined a world without Yuki.

560
00:55:56,910 --> 00:56:01,950
And I thought that I would slip off from my feet, and it was scary.

561
00:56:06,100 --> 00:56:10,180
Would Yuki always be

562
00:56:10,180 --> 00:56:13,000
together with me from here on out?

563
00:56:19,240 --> 00:56:22,220
I understand.

564
00:56:22,220 --> 00:56:25,200
Okay, in front of the station.

565
00:56:25,200 --> 00:56:27,470
Okay, see you.

566
00:56:34,480 --> 00:56:36,060
- Your parents? 
 - Yeah.

567
00:56:37,040 --> 00:56:39,510
They keep pestering me with stuff like, "Are you not getting married?"

568
00:56:39,510 --> 00:56:42,120
And stuff like, "I want to see my grandchildren's faces!"

569
00:56:44,710 --> 00:56:48,050
Are your parents like this, too?

570
00:56:48,050 --> 00:56:50,930
Well, I guess so.

571
00:56:50,930 --> 00:56:53,410
My older sister lives as she pleases, so

572
00:56:53,410 --> 00:56:55,930
they want me to hurry up and get married

573
00:56:55,930 --> 00:56:59,310
so that they can feel relieved.

574
00:56:59,310 --> 00:57:01,340
Is that so?

575
00:57:06,940 --> 00:57:11,050
In that case, do you think we should just tell them the truth?

576
00:57:13,190 --> 00:57:15,110
We shouldn't.

577
00:57:15,110 --> 00:57:18,050
We don't know what will happen.

578
00:57:18,050 --> 00:57:21,100
- But... 
 - Thanks for the meal.

579
00:57:30,430 --> 00:57:34,840
[Mitazono Station]

580
00:57:36,240 --> 00:57:38,210
Yuki!

581
00:57:48,590 --> 00:57:51,830
- Pardon me. 
 - Thank you.

582
00:57:52,510 --> 00:57:54,450
Please take your time.

583
00:58:02,680 --> 00:58:06,680
This is quite a wonderful restaurant.

584
00:58:06,680 --> 00:58:10,690
Well? What was it that you wanted to talk about?

585
00:58:10,690 --> 00:58:12,640
Well...

586
00:58:12,640 --> 00:58:16,440
- Please don't be surprised when you hear this. 
 - Huh?

587
00:58:16,440 --> 00:58:18,200
What is it?

588
00:58:19,240 --> 00:58:20,790
I'm...

589
00:58:22,040 --> 00:58:26,770
- I'm currently going out with someone. 
 - Okay.

590
00:58:29,180 --> 00:58:31,030
And that person is

591
00:58:33,470 --> 00:58:37,010
a guy...

592
00:58:47,120 --> 00:58:49,020
[Akari Corporation]

593
00:58:49,020 --> 00:58:52,530
I'll send you the details and contact info later.

594
00:58:52,530 --> 00:58:54,030
Okay.

595
00:58:59,580 --> 00:59:02,980
- Is that everything regarding what I'm taking over? 
 - Yes.

596
00:59:03,060 --> 00:59:06,000
Thank you for your hard for these past 3 years.

597
00:59:06,000 --> 00:59:08,200
Thank you for having me.

598
00:59:09,000 --> 00:59:12,030
I can't believe you've been selected to be transferred so soon.

599
00:59:12,030 --> 00:59:14,540
The personnel department sure is selfish, right?

600
00:59:14,540 --> 00:59:17,750
Yeah, but working at the main office is a promotion, isn't it?

601
00:59:17,750 --> 00:59:19,830
That's true, but...

602
00:59:19,830 --> 00:59:22,690
Shiraishi, you've always done such a great job.

603
00:59:22,690 --> 00:59:25,610
It's all thanks to your guidance!

604
00:59:25,610 --> 00:59:27,600
I told you to drop the honorifics!

605
00:59:27,600 --> 00:59:31,400
You're no longer directly my junior from here on out.

606
00:59:31,400 --> 00:59:33,130
Okay.

607
00:59:39,030 --> 00:59:41,550
- Itou-kun. 
 - Huh?

608
00:59:41,550 --> 00:59:43,150
I like you.

609
00:59:50,430 --> 00:59:56,380
I still like you after all.

610
01:00:01,230 --> 01:00:06,350
If it's all right with you, would you like to go on a date this weekend?

611
01:00:17,030 --> 01:00:19,050
Is that so?

612
01:00:21,920 --> 01:00:25,280
I'm sorry for not telling you this whole time.

613
01:00:30,930 --> 01:00:33,450
He's someone that is truly important to me.

614
01:00:35,080 --> 01:00:42,090
But same-sex marriage is something you can't do in Japan, right?

615
01:00:42,090 --> 01:00:44,090
Huh?

616
01:00:44,090 --> 01:00:46,500
If you go to Holland or something, you might be able to do it there.

617
01:00:46,530 --> 01:00:51,500
Holland... Europe! I've always wanted to go there with you!

618
01:00:51,500 --> 01:00:57,930
Wait a second. You can hold the ceremony in Japan, it seems.

619
01:00:57,930 --> 01:01:02,750
There seems to be a lot of regulations, though.

620
01:01:02,750 --> 01:01:08,340
Hey, you can also have children through adoption. See?

621
01:01:08,340 --> 01:01:12,320
- You're being too hasty! 
 - Was I?

622
01:01:13,330 --> 01:01:15,780
- Mother. 
 - Yes?

623
01:01:18,240 --> 01:01:19,870
Thank you.

624
01:01:25,940 --> 01:01:27,510
It's on the first train line.

625
01:01:27,510 --> 01:01:30,580
- Okay. This way, right? 
 - Yeah.

626
01:01:31,750 --> 01:01:36,590
Well then, next time, bring along your partner. Okay?

627
01:01:36,590 --> 01:01:38,160
Okay.

628
01:01:38,160 --> 01:01:40,880
- See you! 
 - See you!

629
01:01:42,400 --> 01:01:45,010
- Be careful! 
 - Okay!

630
01:01:50,340 --> 01:01:54,420
We just need to go on with our own ways of life.

631
01:01:56,080 --> 01:01:59,870
I should take some time and talk about this with Akira as well.

632
01:01:59,870 --> 01:02:04,320
[Alaska Fairbanks Aurora]

633
01:02:11,360 --> 01:02:14,420
Cheers!

634
01:02:18,600 --> 01:02:20,940
Ah, that tasted so good!

635
01:02:20,940 --> 01:02:22,610
It sure has been awhile.

636
01:02:22,610 --> 01:02:25,940
- You haven't changed at all!
- No you haven't changed!

637
01:02:25,940 --> 01:02:27,790
- Haven't we changed? 
 - I've changed!

638
01:02:27,790 --> 01:02:30,860
He's the only one who still looks like this.

639
01:02:30,860 --> 01:02:32,610
Also, how's business lately?

640
01:02:32,610 --> 01:02:36,620
Lately? Well, lately... My father's body's getting worse...

641
01:02:36,620 --> 01:02:39,100
I'm the one taking care of the shop now.

642
01:02:39,100 --> 01:02:41,260
So that's how it is... You also have it hard, huh?

643
01:02:41,260 --> 01:02:42,780
And how about you?

644
01:02:42,780 --> 01:02:45,910
Me? Well, there's been the usual.

645
01:02:45,910 --> 01:02:48,880
What do you mean, 'the usual'?

646
01:02:48,880 --> 01:02:52,110
Anyway, let's eat.

647
01:02:52,110 --> 01:02:53,760
It's a bit noisy, right?

648
01:02:53,760 --> 01:02:56,600
Noisy? I guess.

649
01:03:00,330 --> 01:03:02,860
I drank quite a lot today.

650
01:03:02,860 --> 01:03:05,000
Oh! By the way...

651
01:03:05,000 --> 01:03:08,270
That girl you talked to me about, the one from the commercial district. What happened with her?

652
01:03:08,270 --> 01:03:10,090
Oh, that girl!

653
01:03:10,090 --> 01:03:12,130
It failed.

654
01:03:12,130 --> 01:03:14,930
Again?!

655
01:03:14,930 --> 01:03:18,130
Hey, you know...

656
01:03:19,520 --> 01:03:23,440
What even is 'average happiness'?

657
01:03:23,440 --> 01:03:26,060
- What are you talking about? 
 - You've drunk too much.

658
01:03:26,060 --> 01:03:29,000
Are you drunk?

659
01:03:29,000 --> 01:03:32,640
A bit... No, just an example.

660
01:03:32,640 --> 01:03:35,930
For example... Like...

661
01:03:35,930 --> 01:03:41,250
Since it's 'average' happiness you'd have a wife, kids,

662
01:03:41,250 --> 01:03:46,950
as well as a job and a house...

663
01:03:46,950 --> 01:03:50,490
Hmm, more or less, right...

664
01:03:51,470 --> 01:03:53,100
- What's wrong? 
 - You look sad.

665
01:03:53,100 --> 01:03:54,950
Cheers!

666
01:03:54,950 --> 01:03:56,730
Cheers!

667
01:03:59,420 --> 01:04:01,640
- I'm back. 
 - Welcome home!

668
01:04:01,640 --> 01:04:05,260
Akira! Akira!

669
01:04:08,120 --> 01:04:11,950
This is the radio drama that I was in charge of.

670
01:04:11,960 --> 01:04:14,170
Will your name be announced or something?

671
01:04:14,170 --> 01:04:16,420
I'm not a celebrity, so no, it won't.

672
01:04:16,480 --> 01:04:18,700
Is that so?

673
01:04:26,040 --> 01:04:29,270
Oh, this line.

674
01:04:29,270 --> 01:04:34,340
Did you notice? I got it from what you said a long time ago.

675
01:04:34,340 --> 01:04:36,600
I can't believe you still remember that stuff!

676
01:04:36,600 --> 01:04:38,690
It was on the way back from that trip.

677
01:04:38,690 --> 01:04:43,650
You lost both of our tickets. You tried to make a lot of excuses up to the station staff!

678
01:04:43,650 --> 01:04:46,610
Yuki, you always remember all of my mistakes!

679
01:04:46,610 --> 01:04:50,550
That's because you were so cute back then, Akira!

680
01:04:51,520 --> 01:04:55,330
Oh, shall we go back to that sea again this weekend?

681
01:04:55,330 --> 01:04:58,570
We haven't really gone anywhere of late, anyway.

682
01:04:58,570 --> 01:05:02,520
- Well, this weekend is... 
 - It's fine, right? It was fun, wasn't it?

683
01:05:04,780 --> 01:05:08,750
I have plans this weekend, sorry.

684
01:05:36,290 --> 01:05:39,930
- Let me help you. 
 - Sorry and thank you!

685
01:05:40,780 --> 01:05:42,490
Very cute!

686
01:05:43,730 --> 01:05:46,110
Please go on ahead.

687
01:06:37,060 --> 01:06:38,820
Akira?

688
01:06:40,680 --> 01:06:44,350
Sorry, I'm tired.

689
01:07:13,770 --> 01:07:17,690
[Alaska Fairbanks Aurora]

690
01:07:28,930 --> 01:07:31,070
I'm back.

691
01:07:42,240 --> 01:07:46,190
[Alaska Fairbanks Aurora]

692
01:07:50,470 --> 01:07:54,850
What's with this? Are you going to Alaska? When?

693
01:07:54,850 --> 01:07:57,480
No, that's not it.

694
01:07:58,890 --> 01:08:02,030
It would be great if we could go together someday.

695
01:08:07,220 --> 01:08:11,400
Didn't we want to go to a place like this long ago?

696
01:08:11,400 --> 01:08:15,490
I know we're busy right now and really shouldn't be thinking about a trip, but...

697
01:08:16,560 --> 01:08:19,670
Someday, when we have time, let's go!

698
01:08:19,670 --> 01:08:22,330
Someday in the future!

699
01:08:22,330 --> 01:08:25,100
I wonder if it would be best if we went after we're retired?

700
01:08:25,100 --> 01:08:28,220
It is said that it could take several days before you can see the aurora, after all.

701
01:08:29,630 --> 01:08:32,990
Don't you think we'd still be pretty energetic when we're sixty years old?

702
01:08:33,940 --> 01:08:38,320
We could cover the expenses by saving up little by little.

703
01:08:38,320 --> 01:08:41,820
And we could find a cheap place to stay if we searched.

704
01:08:41,830 --> 01:08:47,170
- Yuki... 
 - You don't like Alaska? Would the desert have been better?

705
01:08:48,000 --> 01:08:50,080
I'm fine going anywhere as long as I'm with you, Akira.

706
01:08:50,080 --> 01:08:51,860
Yuki!

707
01:08:55,520 --> 01:08:59,140
I can't promise you that.

708
01:09:06,900 --> 01:09:08,820
Let's break up.

709
01:09:18,620 --> 01:09:20,250
Why?

710
01:09:21,990 --> 01:09:25,960
Do the two of us have a future?

711
01:09:27,110 --> 01:09:30,580
We're no longer of an age where youthful enthusiasm can accomplish anything.

712
01:09:32,670 --> 01:09:38,290
You and I weren't necessarily into other guys in the first place, right?

713
01:09:38,360 --> 01:09:45,320
When you think about your future, you would also like to normally get married and have a family, right?

714
01:09:48,170 --> 01:09:53,530
If we continue on with this fruitless relationship,

715
01:09:53,560 --> 01:09:57,750
we'll surely regret it once we're forty or fifty years old.

716
01:10:02,800 --> 01:10:05,930
To be attached to this relationship...

717
01:10:09,520 --> 01:10:11,330
It's a mistake.

718
01:10:29,560 --> 01:10:33,510
Normal... Normal...

719
01:10:33,510 --> 01:10:36,240
This is normal enough, is it not?

720
01:10:36,240 --> 01:10:38,800
An ordinary salaryman...

721
01:10:49,250 --> 01:10:54,010
Even though he loved me so much!

722
01:11:30,000 --> 01:11:33,520
A life on the rails of normalcy

723
01:11:33,520 --> 01:11:37,020
is something similar to this train.

724
01:11:37,770 --> 01:11:40,120
Once you get on,

725
01:11:40,120 --> 01:11:42,530
so long as you don't get off on your own,

726
01:11:42,530 --> 01:11:47,650
you're automatically brought to your destination.

727
01:11:48,200 --> 01:11:50,680
Itou, regarding today's meeting,

728
01:11:50,680 --> 01:11:52,670
- we're meeting at 3:00 p.m. at Sendai Station. 
 - Understood.

729
01:11:52,670 --> 01:11:54,480
- I'm counting on you. 
 - Okay.

730
01:11:54,480 --> 01:11:58,010
Look at this. Cute, right?

731
01:11:58,010 --> 01:11:59,910
My baby is so cute!

732
01:11:59,910 --> 01:12:03,050
Lately, my baby won't sit still at all!

733
01:12:03,050 --> 01:12:06,040
It's so cute!

734
01:12:07,030 --> 01:12:10,500
